com.ge.dspmicro.httpclient.api

Interface IHttpClientFactory


  • public interface IHttpClientFactory
    This is an advanced feature for using a private instance of HttpClient. This allows for creating a reserved instance (private) of the IHttpClient for a client. The interface is the same but the internal HttpClient and Pool are private and not shared as part of this service. The client that creates a reserved IHttpClient must also call the deleteHttpClient to clean up the internal resources. Note: global property changes to the connection pooling are not propagated to this object . I.e. Proxy configuration, maximum total connections, etc, will not be propagated to this object.
